---
description: Summarise the findings under a directory using an extension tool
mode: subagent
tools:
  - read
  - finding_store
params:
  findings_dir: string
---
// `tools:` mixes a built-in (`read`) with an extension-registered Pi tool
// (`finding_store`, contributed by an installed Pi extension). This theta is
// `mode: subagent`, so the invocation runs the WHOLE callee in a spawned child
// `pi` process that loads the same extensions. Two reach paths work here:
//
// Code-side reach (0.10.0): theta CODE can now call `finding_store` directly.
// In subagent mode a code-side extension-tool call is dispatched
// deterministically through the child's own host agent loop (PIC-61 rung 2 —
// host-loop dispatch): the code-supplied arguments are used verbatim, zero
// model tokens are spent, and the result returns to code like any tool call.
let check = finding_store({ op: "validate", findingsDir: findings_dir })?

// Model-facing reach: the MODEL may also call `finding_store` during the
// query's tool loop below — the callable-set names become the child session's
// active-tool allowlist.
//
// Code-side dispatch is fail-closed only where NO rung exists — a prompt-mode
// theta (whose `tools:` cannot name an extension tool at all) or an in-process
// `subagent fn` inline body; there it refuses to load with
// `theta/load/extension-tool-unreachable`. Listing an extension tool whose
// extension is not installed is a different load-time error
// (`theta/load/unknown-tool`), not a silent no-op.
@`Using the store under ${findings_dir} (schema check: ${check}), list the
findings with finding_store, read any file it references, and report how many
findings are still open in one sentence.`
